	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101898078779748><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101898078779748>RE: info for a first rate newbie</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101898078779748#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 16th 2:19 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>What level are you right now? If you are over level 5 throw the rusty ulak in the sewers and don't look back. As for armor start with simple cloth and leather. You can get leather for free by talking to Cindi in the Kilt Shop in Halas. She will give you a quest to give her polar bear pelts. These pelts are white and can be found on polar bear cubs (about level 2-3). You can also find cloth droping from various low level humanoid mobs like gnolls, goblins, and orcs. There are also 3 froglocs in the Qeynos Aquiducts that drop netted armor. This is only as good as cloth but is a little lighter.<br><br>Don't even attempt guk for several more levels. Check the zone guides for the levels of this area, it's much higher than newbie level. As for PC's, it never hurts to auction for cheap armor, some people just give out armor that is worthless to them to newbies as a good dead. Just watch you don't annoy players by begging.<br><br>It is never easy to start out, so take it slow and try to get all the money you can as you start out. Kill skels and gnolls with weapons that can be sold for quick cash. Collect bat wings and bone chips to sell in stacks as well as spiderling silks. Use the money to get better armor starting with raw silk, then cured silk.<br><br>You can also pick up a small sewing kit for a few gold and head to Everfrost or West Karanas to kill for spider silk, spiderling silk, and ruined pelts. Combining 2 spiderling silks yields silk threads. Combining 2 threads yields silk bandages. Combining 2 spider silks yields a silk swatch. You will never fail when making swatches and threads, and they trivial at around 15. Once you get to 15 you can start taking your ruined pelts and combine them with an appropirate pattern to make your own leather armor cheap. Once you trivial the leather armor (around 26) you can start using your silk swatches and patterns to make raw silk armor. Later you can take heady kiola (you can brew your own) and combine with raw silk to make your very own cured silk.<br><br>As for weapons just keep looking around for better. Ask other monks what they use and you might be able to pick up a suruplus weapon fairly cheap. Above all try reading the equipment areas on this web site and others to get a feel for what you can afford and use.<br><br>Good luck to you.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr 16 14:34:07 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
