	   <tr><td colspan=2>Next time you play, get your character naked, or under, say 10 pounds (stone, weight, whatever).&nbsp;&nbsp;Take a look at your AC, then add those pieces back a few at a time.  In fact, go add a few more pieces into your inventory and take the weight up to 50 or so.  If your monk is anything like mine, your AC is dropping through the floor.  Since Iksar have the naturally higher AC, I don't know if you'll notice as much as my Human, but it will definitely affect it.<br>At these levels, its probably not absolutely necessary to keep the weight under 15, as you might not notice a few AC gone here and there.  But as you get higher in levels, the need for every point of AC is required for survival, so you might as well get in the practice.<br><br>The weapon is a little on the heavy side, and a few high-level monks have probably passed out reading that you were using it.  Also, its a 6/30 weapon, and you can probably do more damage, faster with your fists.  If not now, then soon.<br><br>Good luck<br>Lunar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
