	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 15th 10:33 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Try the other side of the contenent for a while, it's much less populated. You might miss the duel messages and arguing over shout tho since KS'ing and training seems to be sports or possibly an art form in the nro, sro, and the oasis (but I'm not bitter ;-) ). Everfrost is almost as popular as the areas near freeport, but there are so many areas for different levels it's still good hunting most of the time. At your level you could solo or group mammouth calves, orc trooper, orc mountaineers, orc shaman, and ice bone skels.<br><br>Other good areas are the Karanas which tend to have low populations of players most of the time. You could solo gorge hounds and gnoll reavers in EK, or elephants in SK. KFC (the aviak bird house) is very popular in SK and you could find a group quickly there. NK offers beetles which are easy for monks and slow enough to run from unsowed. Just watch for griffs and the occational HG in NK, and cyclopses in EK and SK.<br><br>If you want to try Kunark LOIO (lake of ill omen) seems to be very popular for monks 15-25 followed by frontier mountains (FM) at around 25-30 or so. If you go this way you need to get to Butcherblock and take the shutles to FV. Once there you will need to get someone to show you how to make it past the spiders to LOIO. It's not that hard and can be done with invis or SoW easily, but you need to know how to find the zone and how to deal with the spiders.<br><br>There are so many good areas out there you should really travel around and ask people where they like to hunt at various levels. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
