	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 11th 10:11 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you loot other people's corpses without asking you will get a bad reputation and perhaps a petition or two to boot. I can't tell you the number of times someone has jumped my corpses while I was in the middle of a chain pull with a group in places like SK. When this happens most people usually enjoy watching these loot jumpers die begging for help when they get too close to a TM Gnoll pop, it can be considered poetic justice. If you see corpses that are in the middle of nowhere and noone is near then consider the corpse to see how long it has been there. If it will decay in less than a min then it's pretty safe. If there is someone in the area then don't touch it. Ask politely if they are letting an item rot on it that you might take. <br><br>Some items like runed totem staffs and splitpaw tooth necklaces are lore and will often be left to rot. In places like ME you will often see monks hanging around the entrance asking to loot Goranga Spiked Clubs. Just treat corpses as property and ask politely and you will often find that you can get some good loot without having to face a bad reputation.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
