	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would say that you are fine up till low or mid 20's with the cured silk, but you will have many frustrations especially soloing. I would try to replace as much of your armor as quickly as possible with wu's or better. If you start to notice yourself getting hit a lot of times for a lot of damage each time then you are getting out of the range for you equipment. Your weapons will definitely be effective longer than your armor will be. <br><br>One thing that you might not like is that you may need to slow down your leveling and hit areas for money only. At 20 you should be able to clear out bandits in the Karanas and kill wisps for good money and no risk. Unfortunately, this also means no exp, but it could be a useful time to improve on FD and ID while you are farming money.<br><br>Some good suggestions you can try with only a few hours killing bandits are:<br><br>- Wu's armor pieces around 20-100/piece depending on your ability to bargain and the item.<br>- collar of undead protection 20<br>- Gem inlaid gauntlets around 100 or questable at around 20 at gnoll spires in SK with a group<br>- foreman's tunic around 100<br><br>One recomendation I always make when looking for money is to get 2-5 spirit pouches from a shaman. I tend to pay 1pp/per as a courtesey, but most will give them for the asking.<br><br>Hope this is helpful<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
