	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree 100%, Master Niteklaw.<br><br>If you decide to try to get one, please take the advice that follows.<br><br>I got a goranga spiked club at level 20. It took me 6 hours because I only sent an ooc out once every 30 minutes or so. I also tried to make my ooc's humorous rather than annoying. For instance, one of them was:<br><br>/ooc If any goranga spiked clubs are rotting a crazy naked monk will gladly make the suicide run to get it if you will just let him know.<br><br>As the evening wore on I would changed it based on current ooc conversations and what not. But, and I stress this, DO NOT ooc every 5 or 10 minutes. Once or twice an hour will keep people from getting annoyed, and the funnier you can be the more likely you are to get one. DO NOT get impatient. Quite likely there are people in the zone who can handle the mobs and are also hunting for the clubs. They obviously get first choice on them. If one drops and somebody else gets it, keep your sense of humor. <br><br>One other tactic I used was to offer to help beat on gorangas outside of the groups that were hunting them. Make sure the entire group is ok with this and that you know who to /assist. Not only will this keep you from getting bored, it also shows that you are willing to work for a club instead of just sitting around hoping for a hand-out. <br><br>Another suggestion is to find a necro who is solo fear-kiting. Offer to become a human DOT and beat on the mobs he is fearing. In order to do this your FD skill will have to be at least in the 80's or 90's so that if the mob turns and agros you will have a good chance of a successful FD. At level 20, I took a hit for 123 from a goranga, and I have been told that they can quad for 400. <br><br>Be polite. If you offer to help and get turned down, smile, wish them luck and tell them that if they need anything like food or water you have plenty and are willing to share free of charge. (You might want to make sure you have plenty on hand, I had several stacks on me just in case.)<br><br>Again, if you are going to do this, be considerate. Be funny. Poke fun at yourself. DO NOT spam the zone. One or two ooc's at the most per hour is sufficient. I had most of the zone laughing at my ooc's and got quite a few tells from people who appreciated my humor. At one point a guild staging a raid in the Umbral Plains showed up and pulled a few gorangas for me in an effort to get one to drop before they headed on. I thanked them profusely and kept them entertained while they were getting their groups together. In the process I made a couple of friends. <br><br>I can't stress enough that politeness and humor is the way to go. DO NOT be annoying. Also, if you aren't the only one in the zone looking for one through ooc, leave. Come back some other time when they are gone. <br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
