	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 9th 4:31 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Agro-management is just as much the responsibility of the casters and healers as it is the responsibility of the melees. If your casters continually get the agro, it is also because THEY are handling the situation poorly. Make sure they know this.<br><br>Other than that, Wubao makes good points. It should be mentioned, that generally agro builds depending more on the number of hits, rather than the damage dealt. This is why tanks dual-wield, and why monks should too when they are MA. Have your casters help you here. Make a hotkey that ensures they always keep haste and Damageshield on you.<br><br>Also, when you are the MA, be sure to WAIT A WHILE before letting everyone else start hitting your target. Make some more hotkeys for this. A Monk-MA needs a bit more time to build agro, so when the pull comes back, you AND ONLY YOU get to beat on it for a while. Then when you feel confident that the MoB really hates you, hit your &quot; /g Assist me in killing %T&quot;-hotkey to let others join in. Otherwise the mob will be ping-ponging from caster to caster, and someone may die before you realise what happens.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679 target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev.</td></tr>
