	   <tr><td colspan=2>You'll hardly ever use your training points once you're into your mid-levels and then beyond. <br>Why are those skills so low? You oughta be constantly training your skills from day one. After every level, pick a target, and hit Instill Doubt and Sneak continuously while running around the place. That is what many monks, and rogues do while going across zones.<br><br>IMO, sneak is sort of useless for monks and its only value is to allow you to bank at any of the goblin bankers. Instill Doubt on the other hand is a great tactic for soloing. I don't remember the precise method but there's a whole guide how you can solo with the skill out there on the web. The basic gist is, hit ID, if successful, hit your special attack (jump kick whatever), then hit ID again, and repeat. I remember monk friends who have soloed wurms in Skyfire and giants in Iceclad with that method.<br>&nbsp;<br>**********************************<br><a href="http://jbullions.topcities.com" target=_new>http://jbullions.topcities.com</a><br>"man who goes to bed with itchy bum, wakes up with smelly fingers."</td></tr>
