	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sneak is a situationally useful skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've used it for pulling, for selling, for talking to NPCs, and for getting around in bad places.  It's also not that hard to max out.  We're monks, we spend a LOT of time in our lower levels beating on skill buttons endlessly.  Sneak can be practiced at any time - best are times when casters are medding, when you're waiting around for something, LFG, or on a boat.<br><br>A basic thought.  I have all my skills maxed (except Mend - once it's over 100 it always works), and I use them all situationally.  We don't have a skill I would say is useless.  That excludes special attacks like kick, round kick, and tiger claw.  No reason to work those when you get the better ones.  Dragon punch and eagle strike are used in level 59 and 60 disciplines - the discs suck, but they are a (weak) reason to work those two special attacks.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
