	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101794588766896><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101794588766896>RE: WHAT DIFFICULTY???</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101794588766896#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=140616><span id=Guru>Victorex</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>58 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 4th 1:49 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When you are in game, go to the &quot;original&quot; or &quot;windowed&quot; screen, the one with the border around it and a smaller screen in the middle.<br><br>1) Assign the ability you want to one of the slots in your hotkey bank (lower left of screen).<br>2) Press the &quot;Options&quot; button on the left hand side near the top.<br>3) Then press the &quot;Keyboard&quot; button. <br>4) You will have several screens displaying the commands and to which keys they are mapped. <br>5) Find the &quot;User Defined&quot; keys. They number 1 through 0 and correspond to the numeric keys at the top of your keyboard. These keys are used to access your hotkey bank. <br>6) Click on the &quot;User Defined&quot; key corresponding to the hotkey slot where you have your ability mapped. For example, if you put &quot;Sense Heading&quot; in the first slot on the upper left of your hotkey bank, you would click on the first &quot;User Defined&quot; key. The hotkey bank is numbered from left to right, top to bottom. <br>7) Press the new key to which you want it mapped. <br><br>For example, I put sense heading in the lowest right-hand hotkey slot. This makes it user defined key 0, or the number 0 on my keyboard (not on the numeric keypad, I'm talking about the numbers above your letters). I then mapped user defined key 0 to the number 5 key on my numeric keypad. I use the keypad to move around instead of the arrows, and the number 5 key centers your view after looking up or down. <br><br>One other note, if you are in full screen mode you have 10 hotkey slots in each bank. If you are in the games original windowed mode, you will only have 6. To access the full screen mode, hit F10. This will cycle you through 2 full screen modes and back to the original windowed mode. <br><br>There are instructions for customizing your layouts in the full screen mode in the manual supplement that is provided by EQ. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
