	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello All,<br><br>I just made lvl 17 last night and trained feign death. After flopping around for a while I got the skill up to 25 and decided to try it out on some mobs. In the newbie area in Freeport I kicked a rat (obviously very green to me) and proceeded to let it beat on me. What I found was that at this skill level, it only worked 1 out of every 7 or 8 tries. I then decided to try it on mobs more my level so I headed to West Commons (flopping every time fd reset). By the time I got there my skill was at 28. Upon zoning in a lt blue orc legionnare jumped me so I tried it 5 times while killing him. Out of those 5 attempts, 3 of them worked, the orc just stood there until I jumped back up.<br><br>Now, this is hardly a scientific method of measuring it, and I definitely need to do some more testing, but either I was extremely lucky with the orc or fd worked better on a mob more my level. The 3 point skill increase between my first test and my last test hardly seems like an earth-shattering difference. From postings by Guru's Keyeluke, Niteklaw, and Uniero (alphabetical order, don't want you to think I'm playing favorites :) fd's chance of success is a percentage based on your skill. Thus, at a skill of 25 in fd, it has roughly a 25% chance of being successful. <br><br>Now, I have two questions:<br><br>1) If the success rate is as listed above, why does the skill top out at 200? My guess would be that the percentage of success does not increase at the same rate as the skill does, so a skill lvl of 100 does not guarantee success every time. Also, I have heard that some of the higher level mobs aren't as susceptible to fd as lower level ones. <br><br>2) Is the success rate of fd based solely on your skill in it or is there a check done against one of the mobs stats that you are trying it on? Say maybe against their magic resistance? It would make sense to me if it was, but I'm flying blind here since this is my first foray into Monkdom (yes, that's a word, it was coined in this very forum a while back, check the post by Davel on the previous page :). <br><br>Can anyone give me some enlightenment on this? I've looked through some of the previous postings and haven't seen anything addressing this particular issue. Maybe one of the Gurus could post an in depth discussion on this and instill doubt (since I will be getting that in my next level and will probably have the same questions about it). Also, I didn't see these questions addressed on www.monkly-business.com either. <br><br>Thank you very much in advance. <br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;3 13:40:45 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
