	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rather than go into a long discussion on FD and ID, I'll point you to a couple write-ups that should tell you everything you need to know.<br><br>For Feign Death:<br><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=75" target=_new>http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=75</a><br><br>For Instill Doubt:<br><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=76" target=_new>http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=76</a><br><br>Some basics:<br>Remember to turn off attack before feigning.&nbsp;&nbsp;Due to lag and latency, not turning off attack when you FD usually makes FD fail.  As you level up, you'll find that you'll need to attack off, take a step or two back, THEN FD if you're looking to FD in melee.<br><br>FD will still fail, even at skill 200 (you get 'fallen to the ground' messages at the worst possible times, it seems)<br><br>An NPC spell landing on you while you're feigned WILL break your feign.  Learn to time caster spells - FD after they land on you and before the caster starts again.<br><br>You don't have to stand up to train FD.  If you are FD, just hit the FD button again when it ungreys.<br><br>Instill Doubt is a royal pain to train up.  Burn enough skill points to get it to 40.  You can train ID on other players, or on mobs that are out of range.  Hammer it constantly.<br><br>I'm repeating the guides now, so I'll just let you follow the links.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
