	   <tr><td colspan=2>The guides Master Key mentioned are the best I have found.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would point out one more thing, however.  Mend is based on precentage not FD.  I was hoping that the Alternate skills at 50 will give us something for having mend above 100, and first aid is a step in that direction, but there is no advantage to having mend above 100 as it stands.  FD on the other hand is a skill check preformed much in the same way as other skill checks (taking into account your skill).  There seems to be some anecdotal evidence that either some mobs see through FD even when you don't get the &quot;Uniero has fallen to the ground&quot; message, or there may still be a bug.  FD is great and has saved me many times, however there are times when it doesn't help. For example the time I got off a sucessful FD, only to have an AOE hit my group as they were running, causing me to pop back up and become the center of attention of every mob there lol.  Now I am starting to repeat the guide....<br><br>Good luck and train FD and ID constantly,<br><br><br>Uniero<br>45 Human Monk<br>Officer Odin's Ghost<br>7th Hammer<br>(Hail Raster.  My name is Uniero.  You killed my father, prepare to die)  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
